<body>
    <main>
        <h1>LeetCode 874: Walking Robot Simulation (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                A robot on an infinite XY-plane starts at point (0, 0) facing north. The robot can receive a sequence of these three possible types of commands: -2: Turn left 90 degrees. -1: Turn right 90 degrees. 1 &lt;= k &lt;= 9: Move forward k units, one unit at a time. Some of the grid squares are obstacles. The i<sup>th</sup> obstacle is at grid point obstacles[i] = (x<sub>i</sub>, y<sub>i</sub>). If the robot runs into an obstacle, then it will instead stay in its current location and move on to the next command. Return the maximum Euclidean distance that the robot ever gets from the origin squared (i.e. if the distance is 5, return 25). Note: North means +Y direction. East means +X direction. South means -Y direction. West means -X direction. There can be obstacle in [0,0].
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: commands = [4,-1,3], obstacles = []<br/>
                Output: 25<br/>
                Explanation: The robot starts at (0, 0): Move north 4 units to (0, 4). Turn right. Move east 3 units to (3, 4). The furthest point away from the origin is (3, 4), which is 3<sup>2</sup> + 4<sup>2</sup> = 25 units away.<br/><br/>
                Input: commands = [4,-1,4,-2,4], obstacles = [[2,4]]<br/>
                Output: 65<br/>
                Explanation: The robot starts at (0, 0): Move north 4 units to (0, 4). Turn right. Move east 1 unit and get blocked by the obstacle at (2, 4), robot is at (1, 4). Turn left. Move north 4 units to (1, 8). The furthest point away from the origin is (1, 8), which is 1<sup>2</sup> + 8<sup>2</sup> = 65 units away.<br/><br/>
                Input: commands = [6,-1,-1,6], obstacles = []<br/>
                Output: 36
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int robotSim(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; commands, vector&lt;vector&lt;int&gt;&gt;&amp; obstacles) {
        // Directions: North, East, South, West
        int dx[] = {0, 1, 0, -1};
        int dy[] = {1, 0, -1, 0};
        
        int x = 0, y = 0;
        int direction = 0; // 0: North, 1: East, 2: South, 3: West
        int maxDistSquared = 0;
        
        // Store obstacles in a set for O(1) lookup
        set&lt;pair&lt;int, int&gt;&gt; obstacleSet;
        for (const auto&amp; obstacle : obstacles) {
            obstacleSet.insert({obstacle[0], obstacle[1]});
        }
        
        for (int command : commands) {
            if (command == -2) {
                // Turn left
                direction = (direction + 3) % 4;
            } else if (command == -1) {
                // Turn right
                direction = (direction + 1) % 4;
            } else {
                // Move forward k units
                for (int i = 0; i &lt; command; i++) {
                    int nextX = x + dx[direction];
                    int nextY = y + dy[direction];
                    
                    // Check if next position has an obstacle
                    if (obstacleSet.find({nextX, nextY}) == obstacleSet.end()) {
                        x = nextX;
                        y = nextY;
                        maxDistSquared = max(maxDistSquared, x * x + y * y);
                    } else {
                        // Stop if obstacle encountered
                        break;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        
        return maxDistSquared;
    }
};</code></pre>
